ielts,task2,Task Response,8.0,"Sufficiently addresses all parts of the task; presents a well-developed response to the question with relevant, extended and supported ideas."
ielts,task2,Task Response,7.0,"Addresses all parts of the task; presents a clear position throughout the response; presents, extends and supports main ideas."
ielts,task2,Task Response,6.0,"Addresses all parts of the task although some parts may be more fully covered than others; presents a relevant position though the conclusions may become unclear; presents relevant main ideas but some may be inadequately developed/unsupported."
ielts,task2,Task Response,5.0,"Addresses the task only partially; expresses a position but the development is not always clear; presents some main ideas but these are limited and not sufficiently developed."
ielts,task2,Coherence and Cohesion,8.0,"Sequences information and ideas logically; manages all aspects of cohesion well; uses paragraphing sufficiently and appropriately."
ielts,task2,Coherence and Cohesion,7.0,"Logically organises information and ideas; there is clear progression throughout; uses a range of cohesive devices appropriately."
ielts,task2,Coherence and Cohesion,6.0,"Arranges information and ideas coherently and there is a clear overall progression; uses cohesive devices effectively, but cohesion within and/or between sentences may be faulty or mechanical."
ielts,task2,Coherence and Cohesion,5.0,"Presents information with some organisation but there may be a lack of overall progression; makes inadequate or over-use of cohesive devices."
ielts,task2,Lexical Resource,8.0,"Uses a wide range of vocabulary fluently and flexibly to convey precise meanings; skilfully uses uncommon lexical items; produces rare errors in spelling and/or word formation."
ielts,task2,Lexical Resource,7.0,"Uses a sufficient range of vocabulary to allow some flexibility and precision; uses less common lexical items with some awareness of style and collocation; may produce occasional errors in word choice, spelling and/or word formation."
ielts,task2,Lexical Resource,6.0,"Uses an adequate range of vocabulary for the task; attempts to use less common vocabulary but with some inaccuracy; makes some errors in spelling and/or word formation, but they do not impede communication."
ielts,task2,Lexical Resource,5.0,"Uses a limited range of vocabulary, but this is minimally adequate for the task; may make noticeable errors in spelling and/or word formation that may cause some difficulty for the reader."
ielts,task2,Grammatical Range and Accuracy,8.0,"Uses a wide range of structures; the majority of sentences are error-free; makes only very occasional errors or inappropriacies."
ielts,task2,Grammatical Range and Accuracy,7.0,"Uses a variety of complex structures; produces frequent error-free sentences; has good control of grammar and punctuation but may make a few errors."
ielts,task2,Grammatical Range and Accuracy,6.0,"Uses a mix of simple and complex sentence forms; makes some errors in grammar and punctuation but they rarely reduce communication."
ielts,task2,Grammatical Range and Accuracy,5.0,"Uses only a limited range of structures; attempts complex sentences but these tend to be less accurate than simple sentences; may make frequent grammatical errors and punctuation may be faulty."